# IntelliJ HTTP Client / VS Code REST Client file.
#
# Sign in to the SPA at http://localhost:5173, open DevTools → Application →
# Session Storage, copy the access_token from the oidc.user:* entry, and paste
# it below. Tokens last ~1 hour.
GET http://localhost:9000/.well-known/openid-configuration

@host = http://localhost:8080
@token = 9gF5DqsEvzQ2oLy2P8X1dZUr0_P5q2gR3kGcohWyIG-Sz7FTF77IRIeZv8ZtNeF4RoN-bpBwB3odxfSKWj6YD9N2SRLNsnWmIjZAyzWebFTMhzaFhWi9KhcJNO3YPpn3Lpmmum8G_rq8oIfpf1ivre9p6gb47s-dQOu_XkXcDJoMIa7-RIidFcU_hRTGKE4MnDMCcU-IWzfgjXUiWtwx6r-7mEpd39yUt1q8sjvSQdh46BjjpJmLG6hKrkJ36TnFkb2R0g3oPMuSAEt1odvQkeX_HN0ExpHJmqXG0szJmItBWWo4BRAaX2aQPxDa0xToSseJs9g_mzLz9ecT0OhdFQ

### health (public)
GET {{host}}/health

### no token — expect 401
GET {{host}}/api/v1/accounts

### my user (creates row on first login)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### my accounts
GET {{host}}/api/v1/accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{9gF5DqsEvzQ2oLy2P8X1dZUr0_P5q2gR3kGcohWyIG-Sz7FTF77IRIeZv8ZtNeF4RoN-bpBwB3odxfSKWj6YD9N2SRLNsnWmIjZAyzWebFTMhzaFhWi9KhcJNO3YPpn3Lpmmum8G_rq8oIfpf1ivre9p6gb47s-dQOu_XkXcDJoMIa7-RIidFcU_hRTGKE4MnDMCcU-IWzfgjXUiWtwx6r-7mEpd39yUt1q8sjvSQdh46BjjpJmLG6hKrkJ36TnFkb2R0g3oPMuSAEt1odvQkeX_HN0ExpHJmqXG0szJmItBWWo4BRAaX2aQPxDa0xToSseJs9g_mzLz9ecT0OhdFQ}}

### one account (replace acc_xxx with a real ID from the previous response)
GET {{host}}/api/v1/accounts/acc_xxx
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### transactions for an account
GET {{host}}/api/v1/accounts/acc_xxx/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### deposit
POST {{host}}/api/v1/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountId": "acc_xxx",
  "type": "DEPOSIT",
  "amount": 100.00,
  "description": "test deposit"
}

### withdrawal — overdraw to see 422 INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS
POST {{host}}/api/v1/transactions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountId": "acc_xxx",
  "type": "WITHDRAWAL",
  "amount": 999999999.00
}

### admin only — should be 403 unless your role is ADMIN
GET {{host}}/api/v1/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### authorization probe — someone else's account, expect 404
GET {{host}}/api/v1/accounts/acc_someone_elses
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
